                    </div>
                    <span>It doesn't happen often that I finish a book within 2 days. This time it is because there is surprisingly little new stuff for experienced programmers. It is well written and probably of use for beginning programmers, but as I went through the refactoring patterns, I kept saying to myself: "yes of course, I do that all the time.., where are the flashes of new insight?".</span>
                  
