                    <span>I'm surprised with the high Refactoring's Rating. I've read GoF Design Patterns and Fowler Refactoring is not able to reach the experience. Is simplistic, don't give you nothing new on OO programming, and don't have the category to became a classic.
<br />Perphaps I'm not a great programmer (who knows...) but the Refactoring's seems a child story. I'm sorry, many people talked amazing things of Fowler UML distilled. Perhaps, but this is not the case.
<br />For middle brained, s quarter of programmer, I don't recommend the book. Only if you're interested in something like "which're the refactorings (intuitive) algorithms to implement in some place" try it.</span>
                  
